[thinking] **Clarifying Mockito mockConstruction**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to understand Mockito's `mockConstruction`. It seems that when I use `new Base`, it returns a mock, and the constructor isn't run, which feels off. The default `name()` is null unless I set up stubbing. There's also the idea of a child class extending the base; I wonder if its super constructor might behave differently when mocked. Ideally, it should still reference the real constructor.
[thinking] 
